How to build a shared library from  Pythia (8.185) ready for classloading
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Copy *.h to where_pythia_is/include/Pythia8/

2. Copy *.cc to where_pythia_is/src/

3. From where_pythis_is run:
   ./configure --enable-shared
   make

4. Copy the produced libpythia8.so to where_GAMBIT_is/modules/Backends/lib

5. Match mangled symbol names between the library and the GAMBIT backend system:
   (This step will be automated later...)

   - Compare output from   
       nm -C libpythia8.so | grep 'Factory' 
     and
       nm libpythia8.so | grep 'Factory'  

   - Update the relevant symbol names in where_GAMBIT_is/modules/Backend/include/backend_Pythia8.hpp



